ikers. Today, Chilkoot is an icon. It is thirty-three miles (53 km) of dense forest, rugged mountain, golden sand dune, rushing river, and sylvan lake settings stretching from Alaskan salt tidewater to freshwater Lake Bennett at the headwaters of the Yukon River in British Columbia. Rich in natural and cultural history and protected entirely as parkland, the Chilkoot forms a major portion of the extensive Klondike Gold Rush International Historical Park.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEcotourismzChilkoot Trail. 7aTravel / Canada / Territories & Nunavut (NT, NU, YT).2bisacsh  aAlaska hiking.  aCanada hiking guide.  aCanada travel guide.  achilkoot trail guide.  achilkoot trail hiking guide.  achilkoot trail history.  achilkoot trail.  aecotourism.  agold rush history.  aresponsible tourism.  aslow tourism.  atravel Canada.  awestern Canadian hiking.1 aMahoney, Mike, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aScace, Robert, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781552383094?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781552383094423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781552383094/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles